  "body": "I've encountered an issue that when I tried to update the inline styles of a node, it could lose some of the style properties which may lead to unintentional layout broke.\n\nSay I want to replace an inline-style:\n\n``` javascript\n{\n    'background': 'url(http://abc.com/a.jpg) no-repeat center',\n    'backgroundSize': 'cover',\n    'backgroundColor': 'red'\n}\n```\n\nwith\n\n``` javascript\n{\n    'background': 'url(http://abc.com/b.jpg) no-repeat center',\n    'backgroundSize': 'cover',\n    'backgroundColor': 'red'\n}\n```\n\non an onChange event. And the properties won't be completely replaced/copied during the process.\n",
